---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import SplitPDF from "../../components/pdf-tools/SplitPDF";

const title = "Split PDF Files Online - Extract Pages Free";
const description = "Separate one page or a whole set for easy conversion into independent PDF files. Free online PDF splitter.";
---

<Layout title={title} description={description}>
  <SplitPDF client:load />

  <section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-12 space-y-12 text-gray-700">
    <article class="prose prose-slate lg:prose-lg mx-auto">
      <h2>Extract Pages from Your PDF</h2>
      <p>
        Have a large PDF document but only need a few specific pages? Our <strong>Split PDF Tool</strong> lets you extract pages instantly. Whether you need to separate a single invoice from a batch or pull out a specific chapter, we've got you covered.
      </p>

      <h2>How to Split a PDF</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Upload:</strong> Select the PDF file you want to split.</li>
        <li><strong>Select Pages:</strong> Choose the specific page numbers or ranges (e.g., 1-5, 8, 10) you want to extract.</li>
        <li><strong>Split:</strong> Click the "Split PDF" button.</li>
        <li><strong>Download:</strong> Get your new PDF containing only the selected pages.</li>
      </ol>

      <h2>Why Use Our PDF Splitter?</h2>
      <div class="grid sm:grid-cols-3 gap-6 my-8 not-prose">
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Precise Extraction</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Extract exactly what you needâ€”single pages, ranges, or a mix of both.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">No Quality Loss</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">The extracted pages retain their original formatting, resolution, and quality.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border shadow-sm">
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-green-700 mb-2">Instant & Free</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">No waiting, no watermarks, and no hidden fees. Just upload and split.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions (FAQ)</h2>
      <div class="not-prose space-y-4">
        <details class="group bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer">
          <summary class="font-semibold list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>Can I extract pages from multiple files at once?</span>
            <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-2 text-gray-600">
            Currently, the tool processes one file at a time to ensure accuracy. You can upload a new file immediately after finishing the first one.
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="group bg-white border rounded-lg p-4 cursor-pointer">
          <summary class="font-semibold list-none flex justify-between items-center">
            <span>Will the original file be affected?</span>
            <span class="transition group-open:rotate-180">
              <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="24" height="24" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="6 9 12 15 18 9"></polyline></svg>
            </span>
          </summary>
          <div class="mt-2 text-gray-600">
            No. Your original file remains untouched on your device. We create a new PDF file containing only the pages you selected.
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </article>
  </section>
</Layout>
